    {
      "anchor_id": "issue-gothrumedia-villume-admin-1675",
      "display_title": "Issue #1675: User Detail Should Be Fetched on the Server Only — Duplicate Client Fetch Causes UI Glitch",
      "main_description_html": "<h2 dir=\"auto\">Problem</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">User detail should be fetched <strong>on the server only</strong> during initial render. Right now it also runs again in the browser, pointing at a server-internal address that the browser can't reach — so it fails silently.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Symptom</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><strong>UI glitches</strong> — because the fetch runs twice (server, then client), the interface flickers / briefly shows wrong or missing user info.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Expected</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Fetch user detail on the server only, once. No duplicate client fetch, no flicker.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Clue</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">The startup fetch is hardcoded to the internal address and runs with no server/browser check. There's already a smart version of the same fetch elsewhere that picks the right address per platform — use it as reference.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Demo by Developer</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Note: Fixed. This is due to a certificate error.</p>\n<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"images/image-193b2a76-4021-4c75-8b4f-f5b7d8bee0e8.png\"><img width=\"661\" height=\"154\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"images/image-193b2a76-4021-4c75-8b4f-f5b7d8bee0e8.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; max-height: 154px;; aspect-ratio: 661 / 154; background-color: var(--bgColor-muted); border-radius: 6px\" class=\"js-gh-image-fallback\"></a>",
      "metadata": {
        "number": 1675,
        "author": "alfarez21",
        "updated_at": "2026-06-19T07:21:48Z"
      }
    },
    {
      "anchor_id": "issue-gothrumedia-villume-admin-1676",
      "display_title": "Issue #1676: Unify Modal Styling to Match the Login Modal",
      "main_description_html": "<h2 dir=\"auto\">Overview</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Our login modal has a clean, polished look that sets the standard for how every pop-up window in the app should feel. Over time, many other modals have drifted away from it — different background colors, title sizes, button shapes, and close-button positions. The app ends up feeling inconsistent.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">This issue asks us to bring the remaining modals in line with the login modal so the whole product feels like one coherent design.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">The reference: login modal</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Use the login modal as the source of truth:</p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Component: <code class=\"notranslate\">src/app/layouts/login/login.component.html</code> / <code class=\"notranslate\">.scss</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">What to do</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Review every modal (except for the capital that is on the editor page) and update the ones that don't match so they share the same background, title style, spacing, close-button placement, and button styling — including how they look on tablet and mobile.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Definition of done</h2>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>All modals look and feel consistent with the login modal</li>\n<li>Titles, spacing, buttons, and close buttons match everywhere</li>\n<li>Each modal still works and looks good on desktop, tablet, and mobile</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Demo by Developer</h2>\n<details open=\"\" class=\"details-reset border rounded-2\">\n  <summary class=\"tmp-px-3 py-2\">\n    <svg aria-hidden=\"true\" data-component=\"Octicon\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" data-view-component=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-device-camera-video\">\n    <path d=\"M16 3.75v8.5a.75.75 0 0 1-1.136.643L11 10.575v.675A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 9.25 13h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 0 11.25v-6.5C0 3.784.784 3 1.75 3h7.5c.966 0 1.75.784 1.75 1.75v.675l3.864-2.318A.75.75 0 0 1 16 3.75Zm-6.5 1a.25.25 0 0 0-.25-.25h-7.5a.25.25 0 0 0-.25.25v6.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 0 0 .25-.25v-6.5ZM11 8.825l3.5 2.1v-5.85l-3.5 2.1Z\"></path>\n</svg>\n    <span class=\"m-1\">2026-06-19.14-38-32.mp4</span>\n    <span class=\"dropdown-caret\"></span>\n  </summary>\n\n  <video src=\"videos/video-034fd298-2795-49c9-a26a-9cf656440a72.mp4\" data-canonical-src=\"videos/video-034fd298-2795-49c9-a26a-9cf656440a72.mp4\" controls=\"controls\" muted=\"muted\" class=\"d-block rounded-bottom-2 border-top width-fit\" style=\"max-height:640px; min-height: 200px\">\n\n  </video>\n</details>\n",
      "metadata": {
        "number": 1676,
        "author": "alfarez21",
        "updated_at": "2026-06-19T07:40:15Z"
      }
    },
    {
      "anchor_id": "issue-gothrumedia-villume-admin-1677",
      "display_title": "Issue #1677: Fix: {username}/create page auto-redirects to My Gallery on window resize",
      "main_description_html": "<h2 dir=\"auto\">Bug</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">On the <strong>{username}/create</strong> page, resizing the browser window automatically redirects the user to <strong>My Gallery</strong>. This should not happen.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Steps to Reproduce</h2>\n<ol dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Open the <code class=\"notranslate\">{username}/create</code> page</li>\n<li>Resize the browser window (make it smaller/larger)</li>\n<li>The page automatically redirects to My Gallery</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Expected Behavior</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Resizing the window on the create page should not force a redirect to My Gallery. The user should stay on the create page.</p>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Demo by Developer</h2>\n<details open=\"\" class=\"details-reset border rounded-2\">\n  <summary class=\"tmp-px-3 py-2\">\n    <svg aria-hidden=\"true\" data-component=\"Octicon\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" data-view-component=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-device-camera-video\">\n    <path d=\"M16 3.75v8.5a.75.75 0 0 1-1.136.643L11 10.575v.675A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 9.25 13h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 0 11.25v-6.5C0 3.784.784 3 1.75 3h7.5c.966 0 1.75.784 1.75 1.75v.675l3.864-2.318A.75.75 0 0 1 16 3.75Zm-6.5 1a.25.25 0 0 0-.25-.25h-7.5a.25.25 0 0 0-.25.25v6.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 0 0 .25-.25v-6.5ZM11 8.825l3.5 2.1v-5.85l-3.5 2.1Z\"></path>\n</svg>\n    <span class=\"m-1\">2026-06-19.14-43-45.mp4</span>\n    <span class=\"dropdown-caret\"></span>\n  </summary>\n\n  <video src=\"videos/video-5ff9897e-487d-41fc-be77-66a9b7cf1937.mp4\" data-canonical-src=\"videos/video-5ff9897e-487d-41fc-be77-66a9b7cf1937.mp4\" controls=\"controls\" muted=\"muted\" class=\"d-block rounded-bottom-2 border-top width-fit\" style=\"max-height:640px; min-height: 200px\">\n\n  </video>\n</details>\n",
      "metadata": {
        "number": 1677,
        "author": "alfarez21",
        "updated_at": "2026-06-19T07:46:36Z"
